Module objectos.code
Package objectos.code

Interface TypeVariableName

All Superinterfaces:
ArrayTypeComponent, FieldDeclarationInstruction, Instruction, MethodDeclarationInstruction, ParameterInstruction, ReferenceTypeName, TypeName
public sealed interface TypeVariableName extends ReferenceTypeName, ArrayTypeComponent
Represents the name of a type variable in a Java program.

The following Objectos Code class declaration: 

 static final TypeVariableName E
     = TypeVariableName.of("E");

 classDeclaration(
   PUBLIC, name("Box"), typeParameter("E"),

   field(PRIVATE, FINAL, E, name("value")),

   constructor(
     PUBLIC,
     parameter(E, name("value"),
     p(THIS, n("value"), IS, n("value"))
   ),

   method(
     PUBLIC, E, name("get"),
     p(RETURN, n("value"))
   )
 );

Generates: 

 public class Box<E> {
   private final E value;

   public Box(E value) {
     this.value = value;
   }

   public E get() {
     return value;
   }
 }
Since:
0.4.2
